Add a single-file CTest under testsuite/ctest that preserves the idea of tests/hello_world.cc: define and use an application-owned custom debug channel named HELLO, but do so using the current namespace macro style from example-project (for example NAMESPACE_DEBUG_CHANNELS_START / NAMESPACE_DEBUG_CHANNELS_END around channel_ct hello("HELLO")) rather than manually spelling nested namespace debug_channels::dc. The test should capture libcw_do output in memory, use LIBCWD_RCFILE_OVERRIDE_NAME=$REPOROOT/testsuite/ctest/support/libcwdrc_hello-override during CTest registration, call read_rcfile(), list channels, emit Dout(dc::hello, "Hello World!"), and verify the captured output exactly shows BFD, DEBUG, HELLO, and SYSTEM enabled with NOTICE and WARNING disabled, followed by the HELLO message. Keep the test implementation in one source file unless a separate file is strictly required by libcwd.
